# Security and Handoff Integrity

- Treat credentials and tokens as sensitive by default; never log secrets or expose them to client bundles.
- Encrypt stored credentials using strong encryption patterns (AES-256 + IV) on the server.
- Enforce row-level data isolation assumptions in data access code (agency-scoped access only).
- Client portal access must be tokenized and time-bound (UUID-style identifiers with expiration checks).
- Any file verification feature must validate both required format and relevant metadata when available.
- Security regressions are blockers: prefer explicit validation and fail-safe defaults.
